ached for his alleged neglect of practical issues, specifically his "inability" to propose or articulate an ethics or politics. This book investigates the extent to which Heidegger's thought can be read as a crucial resource for practical philosophy and the articulation of an ethos for our time. Leading scholars from around the world offer a sustained and intensive focus on Heidegger's thought of praxis, working through such motifs as freedom, the possibility of ethics, the political, responsibility, community, nihilism, technology and the contemporary ethos, among others. Ultimately, this volume reveals the practical senses of ontology, and the ontological senses of praxis by exhibiting the practicality of Being itself.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 4aPhilosophy : Continental Philosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Political.2bisacsh1 aBirmingham, Peg, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBrogan, Walter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDastur, Françoise, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDe Beistegui, Miguel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGreisch, Jean, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHatab, Lawrence J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJacerme, Pierre, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKisiel, Theodore, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMitchell, Andrew, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNancy, Jean-Luc, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPettigrew, David, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPettigrew, David, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/re